https://www.npmjs.com/package/@tanstack/react-query

React Query is a powerful package for managing APIs with type safety, caching, infinite queries, and inbuilt state management.
It is almost the standard for managing APIs in react.

## Why to move

One of the main reasons are developer experience, and ease of maintenance. Lets take an example using the current request component in our codebase

```js

const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false)
const [errors, setErrors] = useState([])
const [data, setData] = useState();

const query = useQuery(
   route,
   ...
)

useEffect(() => setData(query.data), [query.data]);

const handleUpdate = async () => {
  setLoading(true);
  const req = await request(...., data);
  if (req.ok) {
    notify("Ok")
    query.refetch()
  } else {
    notify("Error")
    setErrors(req.data)
  }
  setLoading(false);
}

{loading && "Form is submitting"}
{errors && "Form has errors"}

... make a form for our data
<button onClick={handleUpdate}>
save
</button>
```

This includes states like loading and error that is very cumbersome to write and maintain.
Here is the same thing with react-query

```js

const [data, setData] = useState();
useEffect(() => setData(query.data), [query.data]);

const query = useQuery({
  queryKey: ["myquery", "type"],
  queryFn: ...
})

const mutation = useMutation({
  mutationFn: () => ....,
  onSuccess: () => query.refetch();
})

{mutation.isPending && "Form is submitting"}
{mutation.errors && "Form has errors"}

...form

<button onClick={() => mutation.mutate(data)}>
save
</button>
```

Way easier to maintain and check for statuses.

There are a lot of such usecases that will reduce the complexity of our codebase significantly. The less state management the better.

## Pros of migrating

- better DX
- easier for new contributors to understand the codebase as most have prior experience with reactquery
- Typesafe
- we wont have to maintain our own hooks
- easier to make infinite queries
- has inbuilt context, so you can interact with a query from a child component without passing down props.

## cons

- Too much refactoring
- another dependency package.

In the long run, it makes sense for us to switch over, and gradually deprecate the old hooks.

